<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAY 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Last week's government package of measures helpful to Australian wool
producers facing uneconomically low prices was welcomed in the trade as a
whole but seems to have done little to improve demand. Only small-scale
orders are indicated and prices remain extremely competitive. The Australian
Wool Corporation's market indicator was 6 cents higher at 395 cents a kg. on
May 5, with finer margins gaining relatively well. The main wool market
problem of over-supply remains.
</TEXT>
