<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAY 93 / International Company News: Gains expected at Clark Oil
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
HORSHAM Corp said yesterday a strengthening US economy would improve margins
at its wholly-owned Clark Oil &amp; Refining subsidiary this year. In addition,
retail volumes were showing gains monthly.
Horsham, a holding company controlled by Canadian entrepreneur Mr Peter
Munk, owns 20 per cent of American Barrick Resources.
First-quarter net profit was USDollars 6.8m, including special items, or 8
cents a share, against Dollars 8.2m, or 9 cents, a year earlier. Revenues
were Dollars 591m, against Dollars 502m last time.
Clark Oil, a US refiner and marketer, suffered a small loss, while the
contribution from American Barrick doubled to Dollars 9m.
