<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAY 93 / Asil Nadir Flees to Cyprus: Asil Nadir In Cyprus - The route
to escape
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE SERIOUS FRAUD OFFICE: Police attached to the SFO arrest Asil Nadir at
Heathrow airport as he arrives on a flight from Turkey in December 1990. He
is charged with theft and false accounting.
THE COURTS: Bow St magistrates court. Concerned Mr Nadir will flee the
country, the SFO opposes bail and asks for him to be kept in custody. The
magistate refuses, but imposes record bail of Pounds 3.5m.
THE POLICE: Saville Row police station. Mr Nadir reports weekly to police
according to his bail conditions. He makes he last visit onMonday this week.
THE FLIGHT: The airport. At an unknown airport, the Polly Peck chairman
boards a private jet. Within hours he is in Northern Cyprus, beyond the
reach of extradition.
 ---------------------------------------------------------
                WHAT HE HAS LEFT BEHIND
 ---------------------------------------------------------
ASSETS: realisations to date         Under Pounds 100,000
 ---------------------------------------------------------
Amounts held in companies and trusts
and various investment                            unknown
Three oil paintings                                  0.9m
 ---------------------------------------------------------
LIABILITIES:
 ---------------------------------------------------------
Writ from the administrators of Polly Peck   Pounds  370m
Bank debts                                   Pounds  100m
 ---------------------------------------------------------
