FT  06 MAY 93 / Research centres may be sold off
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW ADONIS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR MICHAEL Heseltine, trade and industry secretary, is considering a sale of
his department's five laboratories, which generate business worth more than
Pounds 100m a year.
In a Commons written reply he said the government was reviewing the future
of the National Physical Laboratory, the National Weights and Measures
Laboratory and the Laboratory of the Government Chemist, all at Teddington,
Middlesex; the National Engineering Laboratory in East Kilbride,
Strathclyde; and the Warren Spring Laboratory in Stevenage, Hertfordshire.
Mr Heseltine said that since becoming executive agencies three years ago,
the laboratories, which employ more than 2,000 staff, had 'made much
progress towards becoming more commercial and customer-focused and more
cost-conscious organisations'.
The review, involving independent consultants, will consider options
including privatisation or franchising.
