<HEADLINE>
FT  06 MAY 93 / Parliament and Politics: Disability benefit service
criticised
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE delivery of the new Disability Living Allowance has been a 'nightmare'
for many claimants, the Commons social security committee said in a report
yesterday.
Disability Living Allowance and Disability Working Allowance replaced
previous benefits for disabled people in April 1992. There was, says the
committee, a 'tremendous surge of claims' for which the government's
Benefits Agency was not prepared.
By April last year the agency was already swamped with work and it soon
became apparent that it was in 'complete administrative disarray'.
The committee says it is evident that, a year after introduction of the new
benefit, many people were still waiting for too long for decisions on claims
for Disability Living Allowance. 'We believe that in certain very serious
cases the delays in paying Disability Living Allowance are tantamount to
maladministration.'
Social Security Committee, Third report: Disability Benefits. HMSO Pounds
14.40.
</TEXT>
