<TEXT>
MR PADDY Ashdown, Liberal Democrat leader, yesterday predicted up to 80
council-seat gains for Liberal Democrats in the local elections. 'Liberal
Democrats do better in the ballot box than in opinion polls, especially in
local council elections,' he said.
Decisions on the future structure of local government in Scotland will be
announced in a white paper before the summer recess, it was announced last
night. Mr Allan Stewart, Scottish local government minister, said the new
authorities were expected to assume 'full control' in April 1996.
