</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Khmer Rouge guerrillas have attacked a Chinese army unit in central
Cambodia, the first time the Maoist faction has turned its guns on the
country that supported it for decades, Reuter reports from Phnom Penh.
The Khmer Rouge fired shells, rockets, mortars and small arms at the Chinese
