<HEADLINE>
FT  05 MAY 93 / London Stock Exchange: BAT wanted
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, PETER JOHN and STEVE THOMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Buying ahead of first-quarter results pushed tobacco and insurance group BAT
Industries higher yesterday. The shares, which have languished on fears of a
US tobacco price war, moved ahead 17 to 873p with 3.2m traded.
The market is looking for profits of around Pounds 350m, against Pounds 262m
for the same period last year. Nevertheless, yesterday's rise represents a
relatively small bounce. Although the move by US group Philip Morris to cut
the price of its Marlboro brand is not expected to impact on BAT's figures
to the end of March, BAT shares have fallen from Pounds 10 since the start
of April.
The quarterly results will include a currency gain of about Pounds 30m and
reflect stronger performance by BAT's insurance subsidiaries.
</TEXT>
